    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nvim.ui.select supports async implementation but since there is no clear convention for async within lua (or a builtin vim.async lib) im not sure what this is supposed to look like.\n\nmy own implementation of vim.ui.select uses [artio](https://github.com/comfysage/artio.nvim). after 55ceb314ca96ac45418df00e3a1018e18e89dc9b z= and tselect stop working.\n\nthis is because vim.ui.select starts a coroutine that creates a buffer and handles user input. then, vim.wait stops neovim and prevents the plugin from being able to handle buffer changes and user input. im unsure about what my implementation _can_ and _can not_ do to work with select_blocking.\n\nim sure im missing something and im hoping someone can give me some guidance<3\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ngit clone https://github.com/comfysage/artio.nvim && cd artio.nvim\nnvim -c 'so .nvim.lua' +\"tselect\"\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nselect_blocking waits until the callback function is called without suspending the vim.ui.select implementation\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.13.0 55ceb314ca96ac45418df00e3a1018e18e89dc9b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn.a.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnixos\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
