            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> > of the other popular pickers I could think of (fzf-lua, snacks, telescope, mini.pick) only mini.pick works\n> \n> `z=` works for me:\n\nI can get it to hang on `z=`:\n\n```lua\n-- nvim -u fzf-lua-test.lua\nvim.pack.add({ { src = \"https://github.com/ibhagwan/fzf-lua\" } })\nvim.pack.update({ \"fzf-lua\" }, { force = true })\n\nrequire(\"fzf-lua\").setup({ ui_select = true })\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, 1, false, { \"Hoyt\" })\n-- Run `z=`\n-- Nvim hangs with `z=` showing in the lower right in the cmd line\n```\n\nIf I create a new tmux pane that forces Nvim to resize, it then makes the fzf-lua window appear. Same if I hit `Ctrl+C`. `esc` does not make the window appear. Inside the ui select Window, I can press `Ctrl-C`  or `esc` to exit.\n\nNvim info:\n```NVIM v0.13.0-dev-372+gd44b0d1f69\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n```\n\nOS: Linux Mint.\ntmux: 3.6a",
